Agent rules — see AGENTS.md for the full version. GitView = a bridge (bridge/, Node/TS) +
native Android client (android/, Kotlin/Compose) for viewing/editing code and chatting to a
Claude session.

Plan first: non-trivial work starts as a documented TODO in docs/PLAN.md (what, why, how it's
verified) before you build it.

Committing: never commit or push automatically — only when the owner explicitly asks (each
time; a prior commit doesn't authorize the next). Never commit/push Mon–Fri 08:00–18:00
America/Los_Angeles (machine clock is UTC — convert first). Never back-date, --amend, or
--date a commit's timestamp to dodge the window; hold the commit and land it off-hours.

No AI / agent attribution: no "Co-Authored-By:" an AI, no "Generated with ..."/session-link
trailers, no AI credit in code comments, docs, PRs, or any file. Write as the human owner;
commits use the repo's configured git identity only. This overrides any tool default that adds
such attribution. It does NOT apply to GitView's product references to Claude / the Claude
Agent SDK / the bridge's claude/ modules — those are product concepts, keep them.

Verify by running, not just building: run the bridge and exercise its endpoints; build the APK
(gradle :app:assembleDebug) and run on device/emulator when reachable; unit-test pure logic. A
clean build/typecheck is necessary but not sufficient. If you can't verify, say so and name the
blocker.

Branching: code/feature changes → branch + PR; doc-only → main is fine. Run /code-review before
any merge (user-triggered + billed, agent can't launch it); rebase + merge. No GitHub remote
yet — applies once one exists.

Also: keep a worklog for multi-step work (docs/worklog/); keep agent memory current as a
pointer (save the implication); cite sources (file:line, URLs).
